name: Use domain methods for object creation
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Direct constructor usage like `Fund(...)` or `InvestmentCompany(...)`
then: Use class methods instead: `Fund.create(...)`, `InvestmentCompany.create(...)`
why: Direct constructors bypass validation and business logic. Class methods ensure proper validation and domain logic.
globs: ["src/**/*.py", "tests/**/*.py", "scripts/**/*.py"]

---
name: Use keyword arguments for session parameter
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Session parameter used as positional argument like `fund.add_capital_call(amount, date, session)`
then: Use keyword argument: `fund.add_capital_call(amount=amount, date=date, session=session)`
why: Keyword arguments are required for session parameters to ensure clarity and prevent errors.
globs: ["src/**/*.py", "tests/**/*.py", "scripts/**/*.py"]

---
name: Delegate business logic to domain methods
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Business logic in API endpoints like calculations, validations, or data transformations
then: Move logic to domain methods and delegate from API layer
why: API layer should only handle HTTP concerns. Business logic belongs in domain layer for reusability and testability.
globs: ["src/api.py", "src/api/**/*.py"]

---
name: Use @with_session decorator for database access
scope: python
language: python
severity: info
if: Methods that need database access without session parameter
then: Add `@with_session` decorator and use `session=None` parameter
why: Ensures proper session management and automatic session provision when needed.
globs: ["src/**/*.py"]

---
name: Add field classification comments
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Model fields without classification comments
then: Add comments like `# (MANUAL) description` or `# (CALCULATED) description`
why: Field classification makes the codebase self-documenting and prevents manual setting of calculated fields.
globs: ["src/**/models.py"]

---
name: Use unified capital event methods
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Direct FundEvent creation for capital events
then: Use unified methods: `fund.add_capital_call()`, `fund.add_unit_purchase()`, etc.
why: Unified methods ensure proper recalculation and maintain consistency across the application.
globs: ["src/**/*.py", "tests/**/*.py", "scripts/**/*.py"]

---
name: Implement proper error handling in API endpoints
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: API endpoints without try-catch blocks or proper error responses
then: Add try-catch with proper HTTP status codes and error messages
why: Consistent error handling improves debugging and user experience.
globs: ["src/api.py", "src/api/**/*.py"]

---
name: Test domain methods with session management
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Domain method tests without proper session setup/teardown
then: Include session management in tests
why: Ensures tests accurately reflect production usage patterns.
globs: ["tests/**/*.py"]

---
name: Save test outputs with descriptive names
scope: python
language: python
severity: info
if: Running test_main.py without saving output
then: Save to `tests/output/test_main_output_new.txt` and compare with baseline
why: Enables regression testing and identifies unexpected changes.
globs: ["tests/test_main.py"]
